column1: N: Not reportable U: Unavailable — : No reported cases C.N.M.I.: Commonwealth of Northern Mariana Islands.  *	No cases of diphtheria; eastern equine encephalitis virus disease, nonneuroinvasive; poliomyelitis, paralytic; poliovirus infection, nonparalytic; rubella, congenital syndrome; severe acute respiratory syndrome-associated coronavirus (SARS-CoV) disease; smallpox; vancomycin-resistant Staphylococcus aureus; western equine encephalitis virus disease, neuroinvasive and nonneuroinvasive; yellow fever; and viral hemorrhagic fevers were reported in the United States during 2011. Data on hepatitis B virus, perinatal infection, and chronic hepatitis B and hepatitis C virus infection (past or present) are not included because they are undergoing data quality review.  †	Imported cases include only those directly related to importation from other countries.
